race.comment: Tricky race where the ratings love the very much in-form MAGNARDO (12). Has won four on end at the picnics and is absolutely dominating. Earned his chance here and drops a massive 15.5kg on a six-length win last time so the ratings models are losing their minds. Hard to knock and was saved from a race over the weekend for this. On the minimum should go close. EMERALD COURT (7) is going better than last run and looks a top chance to find an overdue win. Placed two back then was not far away in the latest. Speedy mare who will take catching despite the tricky gate. BALGOWAN (6) resumes from a long break with a good run and can only be fitter. Rates highly on best and with the claim looks a strong winning hope. LUNA FIELD (1) has been on speed and getting run down but suited here and can give a sight at odds. YAMATO (10) is mixing form but has the ability and drawn for a soft run to launch late.
